CLASS WORK

During the same year in which Caesar led his army into Germany‚ he determined to go to Britain. He accord- ingly set sail from Port Itius with two legions, and reached the island in a few hours. There his brave soldiers jumped down into the deep water1 and drove off the Britons who were trying to keep them from the shore. A few days later, a great storm damaged the ships so that twelve were useless for sailing. Caesar caused the rest to be repaired and, having again defeated the Britons, returned to Gaul.
